ISLAMABAD, Feb 08 (APP): Pakistan Air Force (PAF) trainer aircraft on Wednesday made a crash landing in Takht Bhai fields of Mardan district in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province.
According to the PAF spokesperson, the plane made an emergency landing in the fields near Mardan and both the pilots on board survived the accident.
